<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="134" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,310,1141,1167]" box="[189,310,1141,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1141,1167]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1141,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[188,1398,1188,1285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
PROSTOMIUM. Prostomium of 
<taxonomicName box="[527,655,1188,1214]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[527,655,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Ampharete</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like, subdivided by a U-shaped groove; median lobe anteriorly rounded; nuchal organs and ridges absent; lower lip not enlarged and longitudinally grooved; nephridial pores/papillae not visible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="134" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,542,1324,1351]" box="[189,542,1324,1351]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">THORAX. Dorsal ridges absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,651,1389,1416]" box="[189,651,1389,1416]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">NOTOPODIA. Modified notopodia absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1347,1455,1481]" box="[189,1347,1455,1481]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
NEUROPODIA. Neuropodia of single 
<typeStatus box="[598,651,1455,1481]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">type</typeStatus>
, their uncini generally similar, enlarged neuropodia absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="135" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,303,1520,1546]" box="[189,303,1520,1546]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1520,1546]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1520,1546]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1567,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
<bibRefCitation author="Jirkov I. A." box="[189,349,1567,1593]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" pagination="78 - 94" refId="ref9823" refString="Jirkov I. A. 2011. Discussion of taxonomic characters and classification of Ampharetidae (Polychaeta). Italian Journal of Zoology 78: 78 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11250003.2011.617216" type="journal article" year="2011">Jirkov (2011)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benham" authorityYear="1921" box="[676,777,1567,1593]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[676,777,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Amythas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hessle, 1917" authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1917" box="[821,1150,1567,1593]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Neosabellides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,986,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Neosabellides</emphasis>
Hessle, 1917
</taxonomicName>
with certain doubts. However, the new material from 
<collectingCountry box="[587,709,1602,1628]" name="Antarctica" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
available for this study clarifies the position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benham" authorityYear="1921" box="[1290,1391,1602,1628]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1391,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Amythas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is here considered valid, and its 
<typeStatus box="[655,706,1638,1664]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">type</typeStatus>
species redescribed. The status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1917" box="[1123,1288,1637,1663]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Neosabellides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1288,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Neosabellides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been clarified earlier (
<bibRefCitation author="Jirkov I. A." box="[384,531,1672,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" pagination="340 - 347" refId="ref9919" refString="Jirkov I. A. 2018. Redescription of Pavelius uschakovi (Annelida: Ampharetidae). Invertebrate Zoology 15 (4): 340 - 347. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / invertzool. 15.4.03" type="journal article" year="2018">Jirkov 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[188,1399,1738,1941]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benham" authorityYear="1921" box="[189,290,1738,1764]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,290,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Amythas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an 
<taxonomicName box="[377,505,1738,1764]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,505,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Ampharete</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like prostomium but it differs from all other known genera of 
<taxonomicName authority="Malmgren, 1866" authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ampharetinae">
Ampharetinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Malmgren A. J." box="[188,387,1773,1799]" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" pagination="355 - 410" refId="ref10049" refString="Malmgren A. J. 1866. Nordiska Hafs-Annulater. Ofversigt af Koniglich Vetenskapsakademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm 22 (3): 355 - 410. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 32339631 [accessed 22 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1866">Malmgren, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: i) absence of nephridial pores/papillae behind branchiae; ii) middle lobe of prostomium anteriorly rounded; iii) absence of nuchal ridges and any other structures of the prostomium; iv) thoracic and abdominal neuropodia of the same shape; v) absence of modified notopodia; vi) absence of dorsal ridges; vii) absence of enlarged neuropodia; viii) uncini of thoracic and abdominal neuropodia with similar morphology.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[188,1399,265,538]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benham" authorityYear="1921" box="[317,418,265,291]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[317,418,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amythas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Malmgren, 1866" authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" box="[627,957,265,291]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[627,755,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Ampharete</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Malmgren A. J." box="[761,957,265,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" pagination="355 - 410" refId="ref10049" refString="Malmgren A. J. 1866. Nordiska Hafs-Annulater. Ofversigt af Koniglich Vetenskapsakademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm 22 (3): 355 - 410. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 32339631 [accessed 22 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1866">Malmgren, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a pair of nephridial papillae behind branchiae. In this aspect 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benham" authorityYear="1921" box="[713,814,300,326]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[713,814,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amythas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" box="[977,1058,301,327]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[977,1058,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amage</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that is why 
<taxonomicName authority="Schuller &amp; Jirkov, 2013" authorityName="Schuller &amp; Jirkov" authorityYear="2013" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="septemdecima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amythas septemdecima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schuller M. &amp; Jirkov I. A." box="[363,644,335,362]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" pagination="204 - 237" refId="ref10544" refString="Schuller M. &amp; Jirkov I. A. 2013. New Ampharetidae (Polychaeta) from the deep Southern Ocean and shallow Patagonian waters. Zootaxa 3692 (1): 204 - 237. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3692.1.11" type="journal article" year="2013">Schüller &amp; Jirkov, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was initially placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" box="[918,999,336,362]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[918,999,336,362]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amage</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Due to the above considerations, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schuller &amp; Jirkov, 2013)" baseAuthorityName="Schuller &amp; Jirkov" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[189,767,370,397]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="septemdecima">
<emphasis box="[189,447,370,397]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amage septemdecima</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schuller M. &amp; Jirkov I. A." box="[466,758,370,397]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" pagination="204 - 237" refId="ref10544" refString="Schuller M. &amp; Jirkov I. A. 2013. New Ampharetidae (Polychaeta) from the deep Southern Ocean and shallow Patagonian waters. Zootaxa 3692 (1): 204 - 237. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3692.1.11" type="journal article" year="2013">Schüller &amp; Jirkov, 2013</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benham" authorityYear="1921" box="[1165,1266,370,396]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amythas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1165,1266,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amythas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the combination of characters such as the shape of prostomium, the absence of nephridial papillae behind the branchiae, the similarity of uncini and neuropodia throughout the body and the absence of any specific characters of thorax. This is in accordance to 
<bibRefCitation author="Reuscher M. G. &amp; Fiege D. &amp; Imajima M." box="[808,1069,476,503]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" pagination="1105 - 1125" refId="ref10349" refString="Reuscher M. G., Fiege D. &amp; Imajima M. 2015. Ampharetidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from Japanese waters. Part IV. Miscellaneous genera. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom 95 (6): 1105 - 1125. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315415000545" type="journal article" year="2015">
Reuscher 
<emphasis box="[924,981,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
, who disagreed with the fact that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schuller &amp; Jirkov" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[240,439,511,538]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="septemdecima">
<emphasis box="[240,439,511,538]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">A. septemdecima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be settled in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" box="[668,749,512,538]" class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Amage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,749,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Amage</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
